  "prompt": "How can you determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone?",
  "response": "To determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone (also known as 1-iodopropanone or iodopropanone), follow these steps:\n\n1. **Identify the structure of propanone**:\n   - Propanone (acetone) has the molecular formula \\( C_3H_6O \\).\n   - Its structure is \\( CH_3-CO-CH_3 \\), where \\( CO \\) is a carbonyl group.\n\n2. **Determine where iodine substitutes**:\n   - Iodine can replace a hydrogen atom in propanone.\n   - The common substitution occurs at one of the terminal methyl groups (\\( CH_3 \\)).\n\n3. **Write the substituted structure**:\n   - If iodine replaces one hydrogen in the \\( CH_3 \\) group, the structure becomes \\( ICH_2-CO-CH_3 \\).\n\n4. **Determine the molecular formula**:\n   - Count the atoms in the substituted structure:\n     - Carbon: 3\n     - Hydrogen: 5\n     - Oxygen: 1\n     - Iodine: 1\n   - The chemical formula is \\( C_3H_5OI \\).\n\nThus, the chemical formula for iodine propanone (1-iodopropanone) is **\\( C_3H_5OI \\)**.",
